<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
In addition to its distribution in the Philippines, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Appelhans &amp; J. Wen" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Appelhans &amp; J. Wen" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrsinaceae" genus="Melicope" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Melicope frutescens" order="Sapindales" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Melicope frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known to occur in Borneo, Sulawesi and the Moluccas. It typically grows in the lowlands but reached elevations of up to 1800 m in the Philippines. The species occurs in primary, secondary, and disturbed rainforests.
</paragraph>
